    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-01-05T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-01-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="135"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d135">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">839.918/10</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Secretary of the Navy</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Daniels</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-01-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 5, 1921</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: I am in receipt of your
                    esteemed favor of the 3rd instant, in which you state that the Executive Orders
                    issued by the Military Governor of Santo Domingo are calculated to counteract
                    the good effect of the Proclamation of December 23rd last, relative to
                    withdrawal.</p>
                <p>I concur with you in this opinion and have cabled the Military Governor to issue
                    a new proclamation annulling Executive Orders Nos. 572 and 573 and in its place
                    to issue a proclamation requesting co-operation and appealing to the best
                    sentiment of the people of Santo Domingo to co-operate in the high purpose we
                    have in mind.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Josephus M. Daniels</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
